    Team News

    Barcelona
    Bayern
    • Arturo Vidal and Sergio Busquets both return from suspension for Barcelona to boost their midfield options. Busquets will certainly return to the starting XI and Vidal is in contention too.
    • Samuel Umtiti and Ousmane Dembele are injury concerns for Barcelona and neither are expected to be available on Friday.
    • Barcelona did not include a clause in Philippe Coutinho's loan move that prevents him playing against them. The Brazilian will only make the bench here but could face his parent club as a substitute.
    • Niklas Sle made his first competitive appearance since October in Bayern Munich's 4-1 win over Chelsea last week but he is not expected to start here.
    • Ivan Perisic will continue on the wing if Kingsley Coman fails to recover from injury in time, while Benjamin Pavard is ruled out. Thiago will face boyhood club Barcelona here.
    • Leroy Sane is a signing for the 2020/21 season and cannot play for Bayern on Friday night.
    • Alphonso Davies sat out training on Wednesday as a precaution and Bayern will be desperate to have the left-back available here.

    Head to Head Stats

    Prediction

    • Barcelona are in the quarter-finals of the Champions League for the 13th-straight season, a record in the competition, after beating Napoli 3-1 last week and 4-2 on aggregate.
    • This is the first Champions League meeting between the two sides since 2014/15 when Barcelona knocked Bayern out in the semi-final. However, Barcelona have suffered more defeats against Bayern in the competition than any other team, losing five of their eight encounters.
    • Bayern Munich romped to a 4-1 win over Chelsea last week to secure a 7-1 aggregate victory. The Bundesliga giants are looking to become the first side to win nine straight Champions League matches in the same season since Barcelona managed the feat in 2014/15.
    • You can never count Barcelona out with Messi in the side but they have really struggled this season, whereas Bayern are growing from strength to strength under Hansi Flick. Robert Lewandowski has remarkably played a direct hand in 17 goals in seven matches and has a WhoScored rating of 9.31 in the competition.
